	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Orc Warlord:<BR>
<BR>
Ok, I camped this Warlord so long I know what this Orc's eating habits are. (I think he likes Chicken)<BR>
<BR>
- There are various places where the Warlord or his Place Holder/(PH), spawns. 3-4 Spots in front of the castle and 2-3 spots on the side or back of the castle. HE DOES NOT SPAWN IN CASTLE!<BR>
<BR>
- He spawns or his PH spawns ever 15 minutes.<BR>
<BR>
- His PH is ALWAYS an Orc Emissary.<BR>
<BR>
After he is spawned, he stands in his spot for around 30 seconds. Then starts to walk into the castle.  He walks up to the Orc Oracles in the throne room and gets some buffs.  Stands there for around 30 seconds then starts to walk outside. He walks to a small table under the Tower, or very close to the tower.  Most people see him, or is PH here; which makes them think he spawns here or in the castle.<BR>
<BR>
The best way to get him, is to have a ranger or drood track the area for all new pops. Kill any Emissary that pops outside the castle. Every 15-17 minutes one should pop, or the Warlord will POP out side.  I usually stand on the second bridge and track from there. DO NOT SIT DOWN, greens attack. This area is where the PH or Warlord POP the most, then to the right side of the castle; then to the back.<BR>
<BR>
I was able to watch this because I am a high lvl druid and I tracked his behavior to see if there was rhyme or reason to this SPAWNs behavior.  There is and I have shown you the way to get your BoB.<BR>
<BR>
Thank you and I hope this helps you in your quest for the Screaming Mace.<BR>
<BR>
Half Elf, Drood.<BR>
PhantomStar Devoted<BR>
Karana Server
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
